CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1941, pg. 8 reads: "When Lilas King and Clarence Morton married last week it was a happy occasion. Here are pictured the bridal party and some friends...The inset shows the couple sealing their troth with a kiss...- Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bride Lilas King being kissed by Groom Clarence Morton, in home of Mr. and Mrs. Walter King
